    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1961-07-10T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1961-07-10T00:00:00-05:00" n="83"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d83">
                <head>83. Memorandum From President <persName corresp="#p_KJF2" type="from"
                        >Kennedy</persName> to His Special Assistant for National Security Affairs
                        (<persName corresp="#p_BMG2" type="to">Bundy</persName>)<note n="0"
                        type="source" xml:id="d83fn0">Source: <persName corresp="#p_KJF2"
                            >Kennedy</persName> Library, National Security Files, Country Series,
                        Palestine, Refugees, Vol. I, 4/61–11/61. No classification marking.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1961-07-10">July 10, 1961</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>I want a report from the State Department, I asked Secretary <persName
                        corresp="#p_RD3">Rusk</persName> about this, on whose idea it was for me to
                    send the letters to the Middle Eastern Arab leaders.<note n="1" xml:id="d83fn1"
                        >See <ref target="#d42">Document 42</ref>.</note> The reaction has been so
                    sour I would like to know whose idea it was, what they hoped to accomplish and
                    what they think we have now accomplished.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_KJF2">
                            <hi rend="strong">JFK</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
